00:00:00.550 --> 00:00:04.570
Another problem has to do with the fact that in planning your applications,

00:00:04.570 --> 00:00:07.340
patterns are only useful if you know enough in advance to include them in

00:00:07.340 --> 00:00:10.970
your plans. What do you do if you're part way through the development of

00:00:10.970 --> 00:00:15.520
your system and you realize that you should be using a particular pattern. Well,

00:00:15.520 --> 00:00:20.280
you can use refactoring to get you there but the only real way to deal with it

00:00:20.280 --> 00:00:24.700
is to become quite familiar. With the catalog of patterns. So that you can a,

00:00:24.700 --> 00:00:27.270
think about them in advance in order to apply them when you need them.

